Class TestServicePublish

java.lang.Object
  avahi4j.examples.TestServicePublish
All Implemented Interfaces:
IClientCallback, IEntryGroupCallback
public class TestServicePublish
extends java.lang.Object
implements IClientCallback, IEntryGroupCallback

This example class shows how to publish a service and some TXT records, and how to update these.

Method Detail

addService

public void addService()
                throws Avahi4JException
This method creates the EntryGroup, adds some TXT records, a name, a service type and port number. It then proceeds to publish the service. If there is a name conflict, it asks Avahi4J for an alternate name and tries again.

Throws:
Avahi4JException - if there is an error creating the EntryGroup
